!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

quick /kwɪk/

(quicker,quickest) 

1. ADJ Someone or something that is quick moves or does things with great speed. 快的; 迅速的 

例： You'll have to be quick. The flight leaves in about three hours. 你得快点了，那个航班大约3小时后就起飞了。 

2. quickly ADV 快地; 迅速地 [ADV with v] 

例： Cussane worked quickly and methodically. 丘萨恩干得快而且有条不紊。 

3. ADV Quicker is sometimes used to mean 'at a greater speed,' and quickest to mean 'at the greatest speed.' Quick is sometimes used to mean 'with great speed.' Some people consider this to be non-standard. 有时分别用(quick)、(quicker)和(quickest)表示“以很快的速度”、“以更快的速度”和“以最快的速度”，但有人认为此用法并不规范 [非正式] [ADV after v] 

例： Warm the sugar slightly first to make it dissolve quicker. 首先把糖微微加热让它更快地溶化。 

4. ADJ Something that is quick takes or lasts only a short time. 短暂的 

例： He took one last quick look around the room. 他朝房间匆匆扫了最后一眼。 

5. quickly ADV 短暂地 [ADV with v] 

例： You can get in shape quite quickly and easily. 你能又快又容易地恢复好身段。 

6. ADJ Quick means happening without delay or with very little delay. 立刻发生的; 很快发生的 

例： Officials played down any hope for a quick end to the bloodshed. 官员们对快速了结这场流血冲突不抱太大希望。 

7. quickly ADV 立刻 [ADV with v] 

例： We need to get it back as quickly as possible. 我们需要尽快把它拿回来。 

8. ADV Quick is sometimes used to mean 'with very little delay.' 马上 [非正式] [ADV after v] 

例： I got away as quick as I could. 我尽快地离开了。 

9. ADJ If you are quick to do something, you do not hesitate to do it. 毫不迟疑的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： Mark says the ideas are Katie's own, and is quick to praise her talent. 马克说这些主意都是凯蒂自己的，接着便毫不迟疑地称赞她的才干。 

10. ADJ If someone has a quick temper, they are easily made angry. (性情) 暴躁的; 易怒的 [ADJ n] 

例： He readily admitted to the interviewer that he had a quick temper, with a tendency toward violence. 他欣然向采访者承认他性情暴躁，有暴力倾向。 

11. quick as a flash→see flash

